cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.NI, cs.DS

The paper discusses the propagation of Trojan malware in online social networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also takes into account the topological characteristics of social networks (cs.SI) and the role of users and software providers in preventing malware infections (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper uses analytical modeling to study the propagation dynamics (cs.NI) and factors that impact the spread of malware (cs.DS).
